        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6295",
        "content": "On the bough of an apple tree, in the fair moonlight, sat a nightingale, swaying to and fro like one mad with the wine of his own music, singing as if he wanted to break his heart and have done, for the delight was too much for mortal creature to endure.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-low",
